.TH trunc 3 2022-12-15 "Linux man-pages 6.03"
.SH NAME
trunc, truncf, truncl \- round to integer, toward zero
.SH LIBRARY
Math library
.RI ( libm ", " \-lm )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <math.h>
.PP
.BI "double trunc(double " x );
.BI "float truncf(float " x );
.BI "long double truncl(long double " x );
.fi
.PP
.RS -4
Feature Test Macro Requirements for glibc (see
.BR feature_test_macros (7)):
.RE
.PP
.BR trunc (),
.BR truncf (),
.BR truncl ():
.nf
    _ISOC99_SOURCE || _POSIX_C_SOURCE >= 200112L
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
These functions round
.I x
to the nearest integer value that is not larger in magnitude than
.IR x .
.SH RETURN VALUE
These functions return the rounded integer value, in floating format.
.PP
If
.I x
is integral, infinite, or NaN,
.I x
itself is returned.
.SH ERRORS
No errors occur.
.SH VERSIONS
These functions were added in glibc 2.1.
.SH ATTRIBUTES
For an explanation of the terms used in this section, see
.BR attributes (7).
.ad l
.nh
.TS
